author: cbs8
title: Philadelphia Rotary Club gives dictionaries to third graders
text:
PHILADELPHIA, Miss. (AP) - The Philadelphia Rotary Club, in celebrating its 90th year, has donated dictionaries to third graders at two schools this year.
Rotary Club President Rex Rounsaville tells the Neshoba Democrat ( http://bit.ly/1GwJieD ) the books went to Philadelphia and Neshoba Central elementary schools.
The club also recently donated $1,000 to the Boys and Girls Club of Philadelphia and also made a financial contribution to the bookmobile at the public library.
Rounsaville says the gifts are all part of the club's commitment to giving back to the youth of the county.
Information from: Neshoba Democrat, http://www.neshobademocrat.com
